The paper deals with visual recognition systems and the effect of local feature quantization on human recognition performance. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves human perception and cognition, which could place it in the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The use of feature extraction methods and image classification pipelines could also suggest the multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the analysis of the performance of different techniques could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
